value.title: Biden says United States is in a 'dangerous place' and calls for unity in Gettysburg speech
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden warned of the "cost of division" Tuesday in a speech in Gettysburg, Pennsylvania, delivering a call to turn past a moment he said is "neither good nor normal" and unify.

value.title: Federal judge rejects Trump's efforts to curtail New Jersey vote-by-mail plans
value.excerpt: A federal judge in New Jersey on Tuesday rejected an attempt by President Donald Trump's campaign to curtail part of the state's vote-by-mail plan just weeks before Election Day.

value.title: The Point: Donald Trump, dealmaker? Not so much.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump came to the White House promising that he would make deals the likes of which the country and the world never seen.

value.title: Pence team objects to plexiglass being installed for both candidates at VP debate
value.excerpt: Mike Pence does not want plexiglass barriers around him at the vice presidential debate against Kamala Harris on Wednesday, a top aide to the vice president told CNN on Tuesday, rebuffing an announcement from the Commission on Presidential debates that the dividers would be used to prevent the spread

value.title: Tim Kaine on What It’s Like to Debate Mike Pence
value.excerpt: Mr. Kaine, Hillary Clinton’s running mate in 2016, spoke to The Times about what lies ahead for Senator Kamala Harris at Wednesday’s V.P. debate.

value.title: Coming full circle, Trump returns to false, misguided 'flu' rhetoric
value.excerpt: Nearly seven months after his misguided "think about that!" tweet, comparing COVID-19 to the flue, the Republican has apparently come full circle.

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely tweets that Covid-19 is less lethal than the flu
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has consistently downplayed the threat of the coronavirus in public, and it seems testing positive for the virus himself has not changed his tune.

value.title: Bernstein on Trump: He has become homicidally negligent
value.excerpt: CNN political analyst Carl Bernstein reacts to the White House declining an offer from the CDC to help contact trace the coronavirus outbreak in the White House.

value.title: Michelle Obama releases closing campaign message: Vote for Biden 'like your lives depend on it'
value.excerpt: Former first lady Michelle Obama is making her closing message to Americans in a campaign video released less than one month until Election Day, imploring people to vote as she shares why she believes the stakes are so high this year.

value.title: Biden says small groups, PPE, necessary for schools to be open during pandemic
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden outlines his plan for reopening schools safely during the coronavirus pandemic and focused on rate of transmission in the community, making sure teachers and proper PPE,

value.title: Biden describes the first debate as a 'clownish undertaking'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden was asked about his first debate with President Trump, and if he could stand up to his opponent in the future. He said the debate frustrated him but should have described it as a "clownish undertaking" instead of calling the president a clown.

value.title: 'I'll go in a moon suit': GOP senator who tested positive for Covid vows to vote for Trump's SCOTUS pick
value.excerpt: Sen. Ron Johnson, a Wisconsin Republican who recently tested positive for Covid-19, said on Monday that he will do everything he can to vote for President Donald Trump's Supreme Court nominee, Amy Coney Barrett, even if he has to wear a "moon suit" to do it.

value.title: Eric Trump scheduled to sit for deposition Monday in New York attorney general investigation
value.excerpt: Eric Trump, who runs day-to-day operations of the family real estate empire, is scheduled to sit for a deposition on Monday as part of the New York attorney general's investigation into whether the Trump Organization improperly inflated the value of its assets to obtain loans or tax benefits.

value.title: Meadows: ‘Still optimistic’ Trump will leave hospital later on Monday
value.excerpt: Trump's chief of staff said the president will meet with his doctors and nurses on Monday morning to assess his progress.

value.title: Trump's latest political theatrics described as 'insanity'
value.excerpt: Even in the midst of a national crisis, the nation's reality-show president was preoccupied with putting on a little show for the cameras.

value.title: Trump told Woodward in March he didn't have 'a lot of time' to meet with Fauci in newly released audio
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump in March said he didn't have "a lot of time" to meet with Dr. Anthony Fauci as the coronavirus pandemic surged across the US, according to newly released audio from an interview with journalist Bob Woodward.

value.title: Russians ‘Have Committed’ to Not Interfering in Elections, Trump Aide Insists
value.excerpt: Robert C. O’Brien, the national security adviser, said he warned his Russian counterpart there would be “no tolerance” for interference, but didn’t mention evidence of Moscow’s influence operations.

value.title: Dr. Sanjay Gupta: Trump shouldn't be discharged tomorrow
value.excerpt: CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta reacts to a presser given by President Trump's medical team in which one of the doctors said Trump might be discharged from Walter Reed medical center as early as tomorrow, despite the fact that the President has had at least two concerning drops in oxygen levels.

value.title: Trump campaign adviser claims Biden's mask is a 'prop' as President hospitalized with Covid-19
value.excerpt: A senior adviser to President Donald Trump's reelection campaign claimed that Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden uses face masks as a "prop," two days after the President was hospitalized after contracting the coronavirus.

value.title: Trump and the GOP are using Kyle Rittenhouse in last-ditch 2020 voter strategy
value.excerpt: With weeks to go before a chaotic and close election, Republicans are cultivating a vigilante identity — someone who breaks the rules to make things right.

value.title: Jim Carrey Plays Joe Biden in ‘S.N.L.’ Season Premiere
value.excerpt: Chris Rock hosted the first live episode since “S.N.L.” was driven from its studio by the coronavirus, and the show didn’t hold back on jokes about President Trump’s diagnosis.

value.title: READ: Trump's physician says the President is 'not out of the woods' but his team is 'cautiously optimistic'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump remains hospitalized at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center after testing positive for Covid-19.

value.title: Advisers made last-minute push to get reluctant Trump to Walter Reed
value.excerpt: Marine One was idling on the South Lawn Friday as President Donald Trump's advisers were inside the White House making a last-minute push to get him to board the helicopter.

value.title: Trump has been 'fever-free' for over 24 hours, hasn't need supplemental oxygen at hospital
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has been fever-free for over 24 hours and has not needed supplemental oxygen Saturday morning, his doctors told reporters outside Walter Reed National Military Medical Center.

value.title: Pence tests negative and continues campaigning despite Trump diagnosis
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence tested negative for Covid-19 again, an administration official said Saturday morning, after traveling to multiple states for indoor and outdoor events, participating in numerous White House events and meetings and having been in frequent close contact with President Donald Trump

value.title: The Real Nightmare Scenario: A Sick Mike Pence
value.excerpt: The U.S. government knows how to handle an incapacitated commander in chief, but has no idea how to deal with a very sick vice president.

value.title: There will be more space between Pence and Harris at next week's debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and Democratic vice presidential nominee Kamala Harris will be separated by 12 feet at their debate on Wednesday, a source familiar with the plans tells CNN.

value.title: Trump administration puts up billboards of immigration violators in Pennsylvania
value.excerpt: The Trump administration has put up billboards in Pennsylvania of immigration violators, an unprecedented move taken in a swing state a month before the presidential election.

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start
value.excerpt: In recent weeks, Trump has put himself and others at risk by holding mass gatherings, some indoors, and shunning mask use while claiming the end of the virus was just around the corner.

value.title: Melania Trump announces she has 'mild symptoms' of coronavirus
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump said Friday that she is experiencing "mild symptoms" but is "looking forward to a speedy recovery" following her Covid-19 diagnosis.
